FROM jsonb_array_elements('[{"id":"kings-worthy-so23","name":"Kings Worthy","village":"Kings Worthy","town":"Winchester","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"SO23","hubCity":"Southampton","regionDir":"North","settlementType":"Non-City","subRegion":"Winchester","coords":{"lat":51.06576,"lng":-1.30504},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"researched","priceSummary":{"avgDetached":715443,"avgSemi":437883,"avgTerraced":340094,"avgFlat":null,"asOf":"2026-05"},"councilTaxBand":"D","overview":"Kings Worthy is a village and civil parish of around 4,925 residents (2011 Census) in the City of Winchester district, set on the north bank of the River Itchen about two miles north-east of Winchester city centre on the line of the Roman road from Silchester. It was a tithing of Barton Stacey at the time of the Domesday survey of 1086 and the present parish (which includes the smaller hamlet of Abbots Worthy) was constituted in 1953. The older core around Church Lane and London Road sits in a designated Settlement Conservation Area; the whole of Abbots Worthy was declared a Countryside Conservation Area in 1985. Between Kings Worthy and Winchester is a ''Local Gap'' designated under the District Local Plan to stop the village merging with the city. The parish is bisected by the busy A33/B3047 corridor and the South West Main Line passes close by.","character":"Mixed downland village rather than chalk-cottage village: a Grade II listed Norman-era core around St Mary''s church and the Cart and Horses inn, ringed by mid 20th-century estate housing (Springvale, The Pastures) and 21st-century closes. Several streets feel suburban; the older Church Lane end retains a discrete period feel within a conservation area.","amenities":["Cart and Horses (Grade II listed pub, London Road)","The King Charles (second village pub)","Tesco Express and convenience store on London Road","Two newsagents/post offices (one in Springvale, one in older Kings Worthy)","Kings Worthy Surgery (GP)","Worthies Sports and Social Club and Eversley Park playing fields","St Mary''s Church (Church of England)","Jubilee Hall (Worthy Players drama group, three productions a year)","Worthy Down (1 mi) and Winchester (2 mi) for larger food shops"],"schools":[{"name":"Kings Worthy Primary School","phase":"Primary","type":"State (Community)","ofsted":"Good (2022, short inspection)","distance":"in village","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/115922"},{"name":"Henry Beaufort School","phase":"Secondary","type":"State (Comprehensive)","ofsted":"Good (2023)","distance":"1.7 mi","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/116438"},{"name":"Peter Symonds College (16-18)","phase":"Sixth Form","type":"State (Sixth-form college)","ofsted":"Outstanding (2019)","distance":"2.7 mi","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/22/130688"}],"transport":{"commutes":[{"to":"London Waterloo","time":"56m (fastest) / 1h 23m (average)","mode":"drive to Winchester station + direct train (South Western Railway)","source":"https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/winchester-to-london-waterloo"},{"to":"Southampton Central","time":"15m","mode":"train from Winchester (SWR)","source":"https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/winchester-to-southampton-central"},{"to":"Basingstoke","time":"~25m","mode":"drive (A33/M3)","source":"https://www.google.com/maps"}],"nearestStation":"Winchester (2.2 mi)","roads":"A33 (parish edge); B3047 through village; M3 J9 ~4 mi; M3 J10 (Compton) ~6 mi"},"prices":{"avgSold12Mo":462443,"avgDetached":715443,"avgSemi":437883,"avgTerraced":340094,"avgBungalow":null,"avgFlat":null,"source":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/kings-worthy.html","asOf":"2026-05"},"thingsToDo":["Walking the Itchen Way along the river bank","Watercress Line steam railway from Alresford (8 mi)","Hillier Garden Centre, Sir Harold Hillier Gardens (10 mi)","St Catherine''s Hill nature reserve and Iron Age hillfort, Winchester (3 mi)","Worthies Sports and Social Club fixtures (football, cricket)","Winchester Cathedral and city centre cafés (2 mi)"],"placesToEat":[{"name":"The Cart and Horses","type":"Country pub","notes":"Grade II listed, refreshed menu, skittle alley function room, dog-friendly","url":"https://www.thecartandhorses-kingsworthy.co.uk/"},{"name":"The King Charles","type":"Village pub","notes":"Second pub in the village, Springvale end","url":"https://whatpub.com/pubs/HAS/00231/king-charles-kings-worthy"},{"name":"Worthies Sports and Social Club","type":"Members'' bar","notes":"Adjacent to Eversley Park, hosts village events","url":"https://www.facebook.com/worthiesclub/"}],"pros":["Two miles from a direct Waterloo line (Winchester); fastest train 56 minutes","Good Ofsted-rated primary in the village and Good catchment secondary (Henry Beaufort)","Terraced houses still achievable on the buyer''s budget (avg £340k)","Two pubs, two convenience stores and a GP surgery in the parish","Itchen riverside walks and St Catherine''s Hill on the doorstep"],"cons":["Modern estate housing dominates; less chalk-village character than Easton or Itchen Abbas","A33 traffic is constant and audible on the western edge","Detached stock is well over £400k — likely a semi or terrace at this budget","Local Gap policy preserves Winchester edge but limits future growth value","No mainline station within the village itself — a 2-mile drive or bus to Winchester"],"whoItSuits":"A practical fit for a solo first-time buyer on around £64k who wants direct Winchester and Waterloo access without paying the Easton or Twyford premium. Terraced and semi stock here actually lands close to the £400k ceiling, and the Good primary plus Henry Beaufort secondary is a sensible future-proofing combination. The trade is character: this is mainly estate housing, not chalk-and-flint cottages. If period looks matter more, Easton or Itchen Abbas (both pricier, SO21) sit in the same Itchen valley; if budget is tighter, look at South Wonston or Sutton Scotney further up the A33.","broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":"Winchester (2.2 mi)","primarySupermarket":"Tesco Express within village; Sainsbury''s, Middle Brook Street, Winchester (2.4 mi)","images":[],"sources":[{"title":"Wikipedia — Kings Worthy","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kings_Worthy"},{"title":"Kings Worthy Parish Council — About","url":"https://www.kingsworthy-pc.org.uk/about-the-council/"},{"title":"Ofsted — Kings Worthy Primary School","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/115922"},{"title":"Ofsted — Henry Beaufort School","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/116438"},{"title":"Rightmove — Kings Worthy house prices","url":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/kings-worthy.html"},{"title":"Trainline — Winchester to London Waterloo","url":"https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/winchester-to-london-waterloo"},{"title":"The Cart and Horses, Kings Worthy","url":"https://www.thecartandhorses-kingsworthy.co.uk/"}]},{"id":"kitwood-so24","name":"Kitwood","village":"Kitwood","town":"Petersfield","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"SO24","hubCity":"Southampton","regionDir":"North","settlementType":"Non-City","subRegion":"Petersfield","coords":{"lat":51.08088,"lng":-1.17008},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"directory","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"","character":"","amenities":[],"schools":[],"transport":{"commutes":[]},"prices":{},"thingsToDo":[],"placesToEat":[],"pros":[],"cons":[],"whoItSuits":[],"broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[]},{"id":"lake-sp3","name":"Lake","village":"Lake","town":"Salisbury","county":"Wiltshire","postcode":"SP3","hubCity":"Salisbury","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Salisbury","coords":{"lat":51.0972,"lng":-1.94612},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"directory","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"","character":"","amenities":[],"schools":[],"transport":{"commutes":[]},"prices":{},"thingsToDo":[],"placesToEat":[],"pros":[],"cons":[],"whoItSuits":[],"broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[]},{"id":"landford-sp5","name":"Landford","village":"Landford","town":"Salisbury","county":"Wiltshire","postcode":"SP5","hubCity":"Salisbury","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Salisbury","coords":{"lat":50.99892,"lng":-1.84188},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"directory","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"","character":"","amenities":[],"schools":[],"transport":{"commutes":[]},"prices":{},"thingsToDo":[],"placesToEat":[],"pros":[],"cons":[],"whoItSuits":[],"broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[]},{"id":"lane-end-so21","name":"Lane End","village":"Lane End","town":"Winchester","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"SO21","hubCity":"Southampton","regionDir":"North","settlementType":"Non-City","subRegion":"Winchester","coords":{"lat":51.09496,"lng":-1.29068},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"partial","priceSummary":{"avgDetached":1058605,"avgSemi":541803,"avgTerraced":488613,"avgFlat":null,"asOf":"2026-05"},"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"Lane End is a tiny hamlet of barely a dozen cottages on Longwood Dean Lane, in the Longwood valley between the villages of Owslebury and Kilmeston, in the City of Winchester district. Set at around 112 m on a chalk fold of the South Downs National Park about five miles south-east of Winchester and roughly five miles south-west of New Alresford, it has no shop, pub, school or church of its own. The cluster takes its name from the road end — a Hampshire convention for hamlets at the head of a lane. Properties are spread thinly along the lane, mostly converted farm buildings, cottages and one or two larger homes; the area falls within the Owslebury civil parish for governance and the South Downs National Park for planning. The post town is Winchester but the nearest day-to-day services are at Owslebury, half a mile west.","character":"Dispersed downland hamlet inside the South Downs National Park: a handful of brick, flint and tile-hung properties (some Victorian estate cottages, some 20th-century barn conversions) on a narrow single-track lane. SDNP planning policy strictly limits new build and the lane has no through traffic, which preserves both the quiet and the absence of facilities.","amenities":["Nearest shop, pub and school: Owslebury village (0.6 mi)","Marwell Outdoor Activity Centre and Marwell Zoo (2 mi)","Bus stops on Longwood Road (Owslebury services)","Full amenities, supermarkets and GP at Winchester (5 mi)","Bishop''s Waltham high street (5 mi) for everyday shopping"],"schools":[{"name":"Owslebury Primary School","phase":"Primary","type":"State (Community)","ofsted":"Good (2022)","distance":"0.6 mi","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/115934"},{"name":"Cheriton Primary School","phase":"Primary","type":"State (Community)","ofsted":"Good (2025)","distance":"2.6 mi","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/115874"},{"name":"Kings'' School, Winchester","phase":"Secondary","type":"State (Comprehensive)","ofsted":"Good (2023)","distance":"5.7 mi","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/23/136451"}],"transport":{"commutes":[{"to":"London Waterloo","time":"1h 4m (fastest)","mode":"drive to Winchester or Shawford + direct train (SWR)","source":"https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/winchester-to-london-waterloo"},{"to":"Winchester (by road)","time":"~15m","mode":"drive (Morestead/Twyford lanes)","source":"https://www.google.com/maps"},{"to":"Southampton (by road)","time":"~25m","mode":"drive (B2177/M3 J11)","source":"https://www.google.com/maps"}],"nearestStation":"Shawford (5.1 mi)","roads":"Longwood Dean Lane (single-track); B2177 ~2 mi; M3 J11 ~6 mi; A31/A272 ~3 mi"},"prices":{"avgSold12Mo":712724,"avgDetached":1058605,"avgSemi":541803,"avgTerraced":488613,"avgBungalow":null,"avgFlat":null,"source":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/so21.html","asOf":"2026-05"},"thingsToDo":["Walking and cycling the South Downs lanes around Longwood Estate","Marwell Zoo (2 mi) — over 1,200 animals on the former Marwell Hall estate","Hinton Ampner gardens (National Trust, 3 mi)","Owslebury Old Stables café and Owslebury Brewery taproom in Owslebury village","South Downs National Park footpaths to Twyford Down"],"placesToEat":[{"name":"The Ship Inn, Owslebury","type":"Country pub with rooms","notes":"Half a mile away in Owslebury; oldest pub in the area","url":"https://whatpub.com/pubs/HAS/00337/ship-inn-owslebury"},{"name":"The Phoenix, Twyford","type":"Village pub","notes":"2 miles north-west in Twyford; full menu","url":"https://www.thephoenixtwyford.co.uk/"}],"pros":["Quietest possible setting inside the South Downs National Park","Walking distance to a Good village primary (Owslebury) and a country pub","Plenty of footpath access onto the downs from the door","15-minute drive to Winchester and the SWR main line at Shawford"],"cons":["No shop, pub, GP, school or station in the hamlet itself — totally car-dependent","Detached SO21 stock averages over £1m; what little sells here is well above budget","Single-track lane, no streetlights, limited mobile signal in places","SDNP planning severely restricts extensions, outbuildings and conversions"],"whoItSuits":"Suited to a buyer prepared to wait for a small cottage or barn conversion and who genuinely wants downland silence, footpaths from the door and a Good village primary one lane away. For a solo £64k buyer with a £400k ceiling this is realistically out of reach for a freehold house — Lane End almost always trades at the SO21 premium, with detacheds averaging over £1m. Owslebury village itself is fractionally cheaper and gives you the pub and primary on the same lane; Cheriton (2.6 mi east, SO24) is cheaper still and has a Good village school; Twyford (2 mi north-west) is more expensive but has a station within walking distance.","broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":"Shawford (5.1 mi)","primarySupermarket":"Sainsbury''s, Middle Brook Street, Winchester (5.0 mi); Tesco Bishop''s Waltham (5.0 mi)","images":[],"sources":[{"title":"GetTheData — Where is Lane End SO21","url":"https://www.getthedata.com/lane-end-so21/where-is-lane-end-so21"},{"title":"StreetCheck — SO21 1JX (Lane End)","url":"https://www.streetcheck.co.uk/postcode/so211jx"},{"title":"Ofsted — Owslebury Primary School","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/115934"},{"title":"Ofsted — Cheriton Primary School","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/115874"},{"title":"Rightmove — SO21 house prices","url":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/so21.html"},{"title":"Trainline — Winchester to London Waterloo","url":"https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/winchester-to-london-waterloo"}]},{"id":"lanford-wood-sp5","name":"Lanford Wood","village":"Lanford Wood","town":"Salisbury","county":"Wiltshire","postcode":"SP5","hubCity":"Salisbury","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Salisbury","coords":{"lat":51.01108,"lng":-1.86972},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"directory","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"","character":"","amenities":[],"schools":[],"transport":{"commutes":[]},"prices":{},"thingsToDo":[],"placesToEat":[],"pros":[],"cons":[],"whoItSuits":[],"broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[]},{"id":"leckford-so20","name":"Leckford","village":"Leckford","town":"Andover","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"SO20","hubCity":"Southampton","regionDir":"North","settlementType":"Non-City","subRegion":"Andover","coords":{"lat":51.13464,"lng":-1.48516},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"researched","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":"D","overview":"Leckford is a small estate village of around 100 residents in the Test Valley district, two miles north of Stockbridge on the upper River Test. It is unusual among Hampshire villages in being almost entirely owned by a single landlord: John Spedan Lewis bought the 2,800-acre Leckford Estate in 1929 and gifted it to the John Lewis Partnership in 1945-46, since when houses, farmland, the parish church, the bathhouse and most of the surrounding land have remained in Partnership ownership. The estate was integrated into Waitrose in 2001 and now produces apples, pears, milk, arable crops, watercress, sparkling wine and the Leckford Estate brand for Waitrose stores. The Partnership operates a Farm Shop and Café, Longstock Park Nursery, Longstock Park Water Gardens (ranked among Europe''s finest of its type) and a fishing/golf club for staff. Recent years have seen tension between Partnership plans to release Leckford and Longstock land for housing development and a strongly organised residents'' opposition.","character":"Estate village in the literal sense: thatched and brick-and-flint cottages owned by the Partnership and let to current or former staff under the legacy ''houses for life'' scheme (no longer offered to new joiners). The aesthetic is closely-managed, almost National Trust in feel. Building stock is overwhelmingly listed and 17th–19th century.","amenities":["Leckford Estate Farm Shop and Café","Longstock Park Nursery (garden centre)","Longstock Park Water Gardens","Leckford Estate fishing (Test beats)","Leckford Golf Club (Partnership members)","Bathhouse (John Spedan Lewis Trust field centre)","Within the Leckford Estate LEAF Marque Certified farming operation"],"schools":[{"name":"Stockbridge Primary School","phase":"Primary","ofsted":null,"distance":"2.0 mi","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/"},{"name":"Test Valley School / Danebury School, Stockbridge","phase":"Secondary","ofsted":"Inadequate (2022)","distance":"2.5 mi","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/"}],"transport":{"commutes":[{"to":"London Waterloo","time":"1h 10m","mode":"drive + direct train","source":"https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/andover-to-london-waterloo"},{"to":"London Waterloo (fastest)","time":"1h 2m","mode":"drive + train","source":"https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/andover-to-london-waterloo"}],"nearestStation":"Andover (5.0 mi)","roads":"A3057 ~0.5 mi; A30 (Stockbridge) ~2 mi; A303 ~5 mi"},"prices":{"avgSold12Mo":null,"avgDetached":null,"avgSemi":null,"avgTerraced":null,"avgFlat":null,"source":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/so20.html","asOf":"2026-05"},"thingsToDo":["Longstock Park Water Gardens (April–September open Sundays)","Leckford Estate Farm Shop and Café","Longstock Park Nursery (year-round garden centre)","Test Way long-distance footpath","Trout fishing on the upper Test","John Spedan Lewis Trust natural-history walks","Mottisfont (National Trust) ~7 mi"],"placesToEat":[{"name":"Leckford Estate Café","type":"Farm shop café","notes":"On-site café at the Farm Shop with Leckford-produced ingredients","url":"https://leckfordestate.co.uk/"},{"name":"The Peat Spade Inn, Longstock","type":"Gastropub with rooms","notes":"One mile south in Longstock; mains around £19–£29","url":"https://www.peatspadeinn.co.uk/"}],"pros":["Estate-managed setting with strong conservation and farming heritage","Working farm shop, garden centre and water gardens on the doorstep","Direct Waterloo trains from Andover in just over an hour","Outstanding chalk-stream walking and fishing"],"cons":["Property turnover is exceptionally low — most stock is Partnership-tenanted","Open-market purchase opportunities are rare and priced accordingly","Secondary catchment school rated Inadequate in 2022","Affordable housing plans have generated local conflict"],"whoItSuits":"A very specific buyer profile: open-market houses come up rarely and tend to be detached period properties on generous plots. Best fit is cash-rich downsizers, former Partnership employees moving from London, or established families willing to wait years for stock. The Partnership''s stewardship means the village remains visually intact and the surrounding land remains farmed rather than developed, but it also means newcomers should expect a closely-knit, long-tenured community. Not realistic for first-time buyers.","broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":"Andover (5.0 mi)","primarySupermarket":"Waitrose, Stockbridge (3.0 mi); Sainsbury''s, Andover (5.5 mi)","images":[],"sources":["https://leckfordestate.co.uk/the-history-of-leckford-estate","https://leckfordestate.co.uk/john-spedan-lewis-trust","https://leaf.eco/farming/leaf-demonstration-farms/leckford-estate","https://jlpmemorystore.org.uk/content/being_a_partner/leisure/residential_clubs/leckford_abbas/the_leckford_estate","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Longstock","https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/andover-to-london-waterloo","https://www.testvalley.gov.uk/benefitsandcounciltax/counciltax/council-tax-charges"]},{"id":"little-durnford-sp4","name":"Little Durnford","village":"Little Durnford","town":"Salisbury","county":"Wiltshire","postcode":"SP4","hubCity":"Salisbury","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Salisbury","coords":{"lat":51.1642,"lng":-1.78692},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"directory","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"","character":"","amenities":[],"schools":[],"transport":{"commutes":[]},"prices":{},"thingsToDo":[],"placesToEat":[],"pros":[],"cons":[],"whoItSuits":[],"broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[]},{"id":"little-langford-sp4","name":"Little Langford","village":"Little Langford","town":"Salisbury","county":"Wiltshire","postcode":"SP4","hubCity":"Salisbury","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Salisbury","coords":{"lat":51.18984,"lng":-1.7776},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"directory","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"","character":"","amenities":[],"schools":[],"transport":{"commutes":[]},"prices":{},"thingsToDo":[],"placesToEat":[],"pros":[],"cons":[],"whoItSuits":[],"broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[]},{"id":"little-sombourne-so20","name":"Little Sombourne","village":"Little Sombourne","town":"Winchester","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"SO20","hubCity":"Southampton","regionDir":"North","settlementType":"Non-City","subRegion":"Winchester","coords":{"lat":51.101,"lng":-1.47248},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"researched","priceSummary":{"avgDetached":950371,"avgSemi":472304,"avgTerraced":403667,"avgFlat":null,"asOf":"2026-05"},"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"Little Sombourne (also spelled Little Somborne) is a dispersed hamlet and civil parish of 94 residents at the 2021 Census — the thirty-fourth largest parish in Test Valley borough — set on the chalk above the Somborne Stream, a tributary of the River Test, about four miles south-east of Stockbridge and seven miles north-west of Winchester. The B3049 Stockbridge–Winchester road cuts the parish in two: until the late nineteenth century almost all settlement was in the southern half near the church, while the northern Sandydown section was only sheep farms. The hamlet is now best known for All Saints'' Church, a Grade II*-listed Anglo-Saxon and Norman flint chapel made redundant in the 1970s and conserved by the Churches Conservation Trust; it holds two services a year. Day-to-day life is shared with King''s Somborne, the larger village a mile down the lane.","character":"Open downland hamlet rather than nucleated village: a thin scatter of large farmhouses, cottages and one or two more modern properties (mostly large detached) along Sandydown Lane and the road to Up Somborne. Plenty of arable and grazing land, big views and no through traffic away from the B3049. Inside the Test Valley Special Landscape Area but outside any National Park or AONB.","amenities":["All Saints'' Church (Grade II* Saxon-Norman, redundant, conserved)","Nearest pub, primary school and shop: King''s Somborne (1 mi south)","King''s Somborne Village Stores and Post Office","Crown Inn, King''s Somborne","Test Valley footpaths and the Monarch''s Way long-distance path","Full Stockbridge market town (4 mi north) — independents, two delis, butcher","Sparsholt College Hampshire (3 mi east) — land-based further education"],"schools":[{"name":"King''s Somborne Church of England Primary School","phase":"Primary","type":"State (Voluntary Aided)","ofsted":"Good (2022)","distance":"1.2 mi","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/115921"},{"name":"Sparsholt Church of England Primary School","phase":"Primary","type":"State (Voluntary Controlled)","ofsted":"Good (2023)","distance":"3.0 mi","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/116309"},{"name":"Test Valley School (Stockbridge)","phase":"Secondary","type":"State (Comprehensive)","ofsted":"Good (2022)","distance":"4.0 mi","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/116440"}],"transport":{"commutes":[{"to":"London Waterloo","time":"1h 23m","mode":"drive to Winchester (8 mi) + direct train (SWR)","source":"https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/winchester-to-london-waterloo"},{"to":"Salisbury","time":"~30m","mode":"drive (A30 via Stockbridge)","source":"https://www.google.com/maps"},{"to":"Southampton","time":"~25m","mode":"drive (A3057 then M27)","source":"https://www.google.com/maps"}],"nearestStation":"Winchester (7.9 mi)","roads":"B3049 (parish edge); A30 ~3 mi; A3057 ~2 mi; M3 J9 ~10 mi"},"prices":{"avgSold12Mo":743688,"avgDetached":950371,"avgSemi":472304,"avgTerraced":403667,"avgBungalow":null,"avgFlat":null,"source":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/so20.html","asOf":"2026-05"},"thingsToDo":["All Saints'' Church, Little Somborne (Grade II* Saxon-Norman)","Test Way footpath along the chalk stream south to Romsey","Houghton Lodge Gardens and gardens (5 mi)","Mottisfont Abbey rose gardens (7 mi)","Stockbridge high street antique shops and Thursday market"],"placesToEat":[{"name":"The Crown Inn, King''s Somborne","type":"Village pub with rooms","notes":"1 mile away in King''s Somborne; the local","url":"https://www.thecrowninnkingssomborne.co.uk/"},{"name":"The Greyhound on the Test, Stockbridge","type":"Inn and restaurant","notes":"Award-winning chalk-stream pub (4 mi north)","url":"https://www.thegreyhoundonthetest.co.uk/"}],"pros":["Genuinely rural and uncrowded — fewer than 100 residents in the parish","Two Good primaries within four miles plus a Good catchment secondary","Easy A30/A3057 access to both Winchester and Stockbridge market town","Test Way and chalk-stream walking from the door","Sombornes have a tight benefice sharing the active King''s Somborne community"],"cons":["Almost nothing in the hamlet itself — pub, shop and school are all a mile in King''s Somborne","No mainline station; the nearest is Winchester at 8 miles — train commuters drive","SO20 detached prices average £950k — most listings here are well over budget","Limited bus service, especially evenings; full car dependency","Patchy mobile coverage on the higher ground"],"whoItSuits":"A romantic chalk-down hideaway for buyers who prize quiet over walkability and don''t need a shop on the doorstep. For a solo £64k first-time buyer at £400k, freehold listings in Little Somborne are scarce and almost always above the ceiling; King''s Somborne itself (1 mi, same SO20) has a more varied housing stock including some terraces that come into range, while Houghton or Stockbridge (4 mi) trade pricier still. For better value with a similar Test Valley feel, look at Broughton (SO20) or Sherfield English (SO51) further south-west.","broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":"Winchester (7.9 mi)","primarySupermarket":"Co-op, High Street, Stockbridge (4.0 mi)","images":[],"sources":[{"title":"Test Valley BC — King''s Somborne, Little Somborne and Ashley Parish Profile 2021","url":"https://www.testvalley.gov.uk/assets/attach/15335/kings-somborne-little-somborne-and-ashley-parish-profile-2021.pdf"},{"title":"Wikipedia — All Saints Church, Little Somborne","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/All_Saints_Church,_Little_Somborne"},{"title":"King''s Somborne Parish Council — About","url":"https://kingssomborne-pc.gov.uk/about-2/"},{"title":"Rightmove — SO20 house prices","url":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/so20.html"},{"title":"Trainline — Winchester to London Waterloo","url":"https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/winchester-to-london-waterloo"}]}]'::jsonb) AS value;

